Pre-Game Insights: The match between Algeria and South Africa is scheduled for March 26, 2024, at 22:00 local time at the Nelson Mandela Stadium near Algiers.
Algeria is looking to rebuild and continue their winning streak after a recent victory against Bolivia.
South Africa, a surprise semi-finalist in the 2024 CAN, aims to test their strength against Algeria.
The absence of Amine Gouiri due to family reasons could be a challenge for Algeria.
Hugo Broos, the South African coach, is expected to field his strongest team.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match will be broadcast live and free on TV 1 (Programme national), TV 6, and L’Equipe Web.
